{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idef912207-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"104906"},"text":"§ 104906.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Protection of right of individuals to bear arms","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idef912208-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Findings","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Congress finds the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef912209-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The 2d amendment to the Constitution provides that “the right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Section 2.4(a)(1) of title 36, Code of Federal Regulations, provides that “except as otherwise provided in this section and parts 7 (special regulations) and 13 (Alaska regulations), the following are prohibited: (i) Possessing a weapon, trap or net (ii) Carrying a weapon, trap or net (iii) Using a weapon, trap or net”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220b-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The regulations described in paragraph (2) prevent individuals complying with Federal and State laws from exercising the 2d amendment rights of the individuals while at System units.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220c-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The existence of different laws relating to the transportation and possession of firearms at different System units entrapped law-abiding gun owners while at System units.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220d-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Although the Bush administration issued new regulations relating to the 2d amendment rights of law-abiding citizens in System units that went into effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-01-09"},"text":"January 9, 2009","children":[],"tail":"—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220e-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/5/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-03-19"},"text":"March 19, 2009","children":[],"tail":", the United States District Court for the District of Columbia granted a preliminary injunction with respect to the implementation and enforcement of the new regulations; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idef91220f-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/5/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the new regulations—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idef912210-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/5/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are under review by the Obama administration; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idef912211-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/5/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may be altered.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef912212-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Congress needs to weigh in on the new regulations to ensure that unelected bureaucrats and judges cannot again override the 2d amendment rights of law-abiding citizens on 83,600,000 acres of System land.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef912213-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Federal laws should make it clear that the 2d amendment rights of an individual at a System unit should not be infringed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idef912214-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Protection of Right of Individuals To Bear Arms in System Units","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall not promulgate or enforce any regulation that prohibits an individual from possessing a firearm, including an assembled or functional firearm, in any System unit if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef912215-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the individual is not otherwise prohibited by law from possessing the firearm; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef912216-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s104906/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the possession of the firearm is in compliance with the law of the State in which the System unit is located.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idef912217-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3168"},"text":"128 Stat. 3168","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idef912218-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idef912219-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idef91221a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"104906","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1a–7b"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1a–7b","children":[],"tail":" (relating to National Park System)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/24/tV/s512"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–24, title V, § 512","children":[],"tail":" (relating to National Park System), "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"May 22, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1764"},"text":"123 Stat. 1764","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(5)(B)(i), the words “the Obama administration” are substituted for “the administration” for clarity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
